{
  "page": "The hammer and the anvil",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Young_Hammer_and_Anvil_by_volukyrja.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/32/Young_Hammer_and_Anvil_by_volukyrja.jpg/300px-Young_Hammer_and_Anvil_by_volukyrja.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"384\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/32/Young_Hammer_and_Anvil_by_volukyrja.jpg/450px-Young_Hammer_and_Anvil_by_volukyrja.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/32/Young_Hammer_and_Anvil_by_volukyrja.jpg/600px-Young_Hammer_and_Anvil_by_volukyrja.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Young_Hammer_and_Anvil_by_volukyrja.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The young Princes <a href=\"/index.php/Baelor_Targaryen_(son_of_Daeron_II)\" title=\"Baelor Targaryen (son of Daeron II)\">Baelor</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Maekar_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Maekar I Targaryen\">Maekar Targaryen</a> made their names as \"the hammer and the anvil\" by volukyrja</div></div></div>\n<p><b>The hammer and the anvil</b> is a song about the strategy used by Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Baelor_Targaryen_(son_of_Daeron_II)\" title=\"Baelor Targaryen (son of Daeron II)\">Baelor Targaryen</a> and Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Maekar_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Maekar I Targaryen\">Maekar Targaryen</a> during the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_of_the_Redgrass_Field\" title=\"Battle of the Redgrass Field\">Battle of the Redgrass Field</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Recent_events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#The_Winds_of_Winter\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>The Winds of Winter</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=The_hammer_and_the_anvil&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_of_the_Redgrass_Field\" title=\"Battle of the Redgrass Field\">Battle of the Redgrass Field</a> was a battle fought during the <a href=\"/index.php/First_Blackfyre_Rebellion\" title=\"First Blackfyre Rebellion\">First Blackfyre Rebellion</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/196_AC\" title=\"196 AC\">196&#160;AC</a>. Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Baelor_Targaryen_(son_of_Daeron_II)\" title=\"Baelor Targaryen (son of Daeron II)\">Baelor Targaryen</a> (<i>the hammer</i>) led <a href=\"/index.php/Dorne\" title=\"Dorne\">Dornish</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Spear\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Spear\">spearmen</a> against the rear of <a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_I_Blackfyre\" title=\"Daemon I Blackfyre\">Daemon Blackfyre</a>'s rebel army and crushed it against the shield wall of Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Maekar_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Maekar I Targaryen\">Maekar Targaryen</a> (<i>the anvil</i>). However, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Eustace_Osgrey\" title=\"Eustace Osgrey\">Eustace Osgrey</a> felt the singers left out much from what actually happened, including Daemon's actions in the battle and how <a href=\"/index.php/Brynden_Rivers\" title=\"Brynden Rivers\">Brynden Rivers</a> and his <a href=\"/index.php/Raven%27s_Teeth\" title=\"Raven&#39;s Teeth\">Raven's Teeth</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Archer\" title=\"Archer\">archers</a> slew Daemon and his sons.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_events\">Recent events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=The_hammer_and_the_anvil&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"The_Winds_of_Winter\"><i>The Winds of Winter</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=The_hammer_and_the_anvil&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: The Winds of Winter\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<table style=\"margin: 4px 10%; border: 1px solid #aaa; background:#fbfbfb;\"><tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"padding: 2px 0 2px 0.5em;border-left: 10px solid #f28500;\">\n<div style=\"width: 50px;\"><img alt=\"Content.png\" src=\"/images/c/cc/Content.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" />\n</div></td><td style=\"border: none; padding: 0.25em 0.9em; width: 100%;\"> <b>Warning</b> <br /> This information has thus far been released in a sample chapter for <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Winds_of_Winter\" title=\"The Winds of Winter\">The Winds of Winter</a></i>, and might therefore not be in finalized form. Keep in mind that the content as described below is still subject to change.</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Barristan_Selmy\" title=\"Barristan Selmy\">Barristan Selmy</a> and the troops of <a href=\"/index.php/Meereen\" title=\"Meereen\">Meereen</a> attack the armies of <a href=\"/index.php/Yunkai\" title=\"Yunkai\">Yunkai</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_of_Fire\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Battle of Fire\">Battle of Fire</a>. Near the end of the battle, Barristan learns that <a href=\"/index.php/Ship\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ship\">ships</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Greyjoy\" title=\"House Greyjoy\">House Greyjoy</a> have arrived in <a href=\"/index.php/Slaver%27s_Bay\" title=\"Slaver&#39;s Bay\">the bay</a>, and the <a href=\"/index.php/Ironmen\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ironmen\">ironmen</a> are coming ashore to fight the Yunkish. Barristan gleefully exclaims, <i>“It’s like Baelor Breakspear and Prince Maekar, the hammer and the anvil. We have them! We have them!”</i><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwow.5B.5Bbarristan_ii_.28the_winds_of_winter.29.7Cbarristan_ii.5D.5D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwow.5B.5Bbarristan_ii_.28the_winds_of_winter.29.7Cbarristan_ii.5D.5D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=The_hammer_and_the_anvil&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Dunk</b>: I'd always heard that it was Baelor Breakspear who won the battle. Him and Prince Maekar.<br /><b>Eustace</b>: The hammer and the anvil? The singers leave out much and more. [&#8230;] The singers can go on about their hammer and their anvil, ser, but it was the kinslayer who turned the tide with a white arrow and a black spell.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Duncan_the_Tall\" title=\"Duncan the Tall\">Duncan the Tall</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Eustace_Osgrey\" title=\"Eustace Osgrey\">Eustace Osgrey</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=The_hammer_and_the_anvil&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Sworn_Sword\" title=\"The Sworn Sword\">The Sworn Sword</a></i>.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwow.5B.5Bbarristan_ii_.28the_winds_of_winter.29.7Cbarristan_ii.5D.5D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwow.5B.5Bbarristan_ii_.28the_winds_of_winter.29.7Cbarristan_ii.5D.5D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Winds_of_Winter\" title=\"The Winds of Winter\">The Winds of Winter</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php?title=The_Winds_of_Winter-Chapter&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"The Winds of Winter-Chapter (page does not exist)\">Chapter </a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Barristan_II_(The_Winds_of_Winter)\" title=\"Barristan II (The Winds of Winter)\">Barristan II</a>.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260403135038\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.035 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.057 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 286/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 9016/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 3491/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 1168/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 8/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 1844/5000000 bytes\nLua time usage: 0.010/7.000 seconds\nLua virtual size: 4.5 MB/50 MB\nLua estimated memory usage: 0 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   38.056      1 -total\n 70.98%   27.014      1 Template:Date\n 16.80%    6.392      4 Template:Ref\n  8.90%    3.388      4 Template:Ref/core\n  4.85%    1.847      1 Template:References\n  4.75%    1.806      1 Template:Warning/twow\n  3.85%    1.465      1 Template:Quote\n  3.49%    1.330      1 Template:Warning\n  2.24%    0.853      1 Template:Mbox\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key westeros_awoiaftest-mw_:pcache:idhash:6526-0!canonical and timestamp 20260403135038 and revision id 334008\n -->\n",
